Police in Burumba area, Busia county have recovered an ak 47 riffle, three arrows, a Uganda registered saloon car and arrested three people. It is alleged that the recovered weapons have been used in several criminal activities that have happened in recent days in Matayos, Butula and Funyula areas. Busia police commandant John Nyoike said the three suspects are in custody awaiting to be arraigned in court.